General Notice

This license stands as the official license representing legal and moral obligations that must be upheld by all working contributors and licensees, along with the general public. 

Main Proprietries Of This License

Only those contributing to the Staff of the Khmer-speaking SCP Branch who are invited to this repository may edit or add code. Forking this repository is prohibited by community standards. All forks of this repository must be made by Staff members and approved by Staff Members via a voting system which follows the options of yeah (accept/agree), nah (decline/disagree) and abstain (vote not to vote).

Forking may not be allowed due to themes for the site going to be changed daily for certain holidays or events. the CSS file is where the themes are currently stored. 

This site is not an engine and does not support multiple sites running on it. This is now addressed and should be a staple kept alive in the disciplinary rules.

This repository is purely only public to show off content, not to be selfish, but so people can request to become a contributor and we can prove it exists without having to make it public. 

This repository is not a place to advertise. You must respect the rules and moral standards of the SCP Wiki and it's branches. 

This site is copyrighted. Any fork, edit, or "copycat" repository is deemed an illegality. 

Naivety is understandable for our main site (SCP-KM). If you joined our main site, but were slightly underinformed or naive, it is fine. We will give you a 48-hour grace period where you will have the opportunity to remove your works onto Google Docs for future reference. We can then ban you but with a legitimate reason which will help you stay safe. If you have only just realising, you can ask to be removed from the site's members list without being banned, allowing you to reapply in the future whether or not you were banned. This may apply to this site within Staff discretion and discussion. 

Whitewashing media on this site and our main site is considered a secondary illegality which can get you removed from our technical team or from a Staff position in general, with a five-month ban at minimum and a permaban (permanent ban) at the maximum depending on the severity of the situation.

Media on this site is compatible with Creative Commons Attribution ShareALike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0) but images must be non-reproduced. Original artwork posted to this site is the fully copyrightable exception. Works in the Public Domain or in dedication to the Public Domain (CC0) must be cited with a Wikimedia or Site link.

This license must have a translation into Khmer (km) on the site itself, so that Khmer contributors who visit this English-first Staff Site and do not know English very well can understand. 

Forums must use a DeepL-utilised translation tool which can help soften the blow when trying to understand something in English when Khmer is your first language. The translation tool must use DeepL-compatibility for foreign languages but the tool should be able to translate into Khmer accurately on its own. 

Thou Parody shall not be Not Safe For Work (NSFW) as NSFW is banned on our main site with the exception being the English heritage collection for original SCPs. 

Parody policies must be voted on for SCPKhmer Netter / Khmernetter (SCPKhmer Better) by Staff the night before April 1st and removed the following day within discretion of local timezones. Themes for April 1st (or April Fools) are voted on at the start of each year in preparation for the event. 

Properties (site domains and more) owned by the SCP-KM staff should not be tried for purchase if the domain expires. This is seen as an immorality. 

To be in line with our Age Policy on the main site, you must be at least 14 years old to contribute as this aligns with the Cambodian Age of Responsibility. 

Additional Proprietries

"Property" is considered by elevation of purchase, not capitalist radicalism. Radicalism or its promotion is considered illegal via technical standards. 

Spamming on the forums of this site is against community rules and is a violation of them. 

Maintain decency. While "degenerate" can be a good thing, it is mainly used as a slur with intention to target people. 

